      <hedline>
        <hl1>Left Bank Hotel</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Robert K Brown letter on September 17 Travel Advisory column holds Paris's Hotel Pont Royal is not what it used to be (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor: Regarding the Hotel Pont Royal (Travel Advisory, Sept. 17): before I even arrived at the hotel three months ago, there was a problem. No one at the hotel had checked the e-mail, and so they failed to make the restaurant reservations I had requested.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor: Regarding the Hotel Pont Royal (Travel Advisory, Sept. 17): before I even arrived at the hotel three months ago, there was a problem. No one at the hotel had checked the e-mail, and so they failed to make the restaurant reservations I had requested.</p>
        <p>Once there, I saw that the hotel's refurbishment had destroyed the large, high-ceiling Belle Epoque rooms to create small, standardized, charmless cookie-cutter ones. Over the bed they had placed a tasteless, indeed ugly, print of a sexpot in a diaphanous dress sprawled out in front of the Pont Royal.</p>
        <p>ROBERT K. BROWN  New York, N.Y.</p>
      </block>
